# 17. AI Summary

The AI Engine is designed to convert large volumes of multilingual citizen questions into structured intelligence through language detection, normalization, semantic clustering, department mapping, scheme recognition, trend analysis, and executive summaries. It operates asynchronously, preserves original submissions, supports human review, and provides reliable, scalable insights that help government officials understand public information needs without replacing existing grievance or support systems.
